100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 1, 1925, a significant diplomatic development unfolded as the League of Nations continued to grapple with the aftermath of World War I, focusing on disarmament talks among member nations. In the United States, Prohibition enforcement remained a contentious issue, with reports of increased illegal speakeasies and bootlegging operations. Meanwhile, in Germany, the political landscape was tense as the Weimar Republic faced economic challenges, fueling discontent among the populace.
